Well-informed @melchorcope: &ldquo;The next player to leave Real Madrid this summer will be Dani Ceballos. An operation that could be closed next week when the player gives his final decision. #AFC have &lsquo;slight advantage&rsquo; over Spurs in the race.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Melchor Ruiz [COPE]: &ldquo;Dani Ceballos will leave on a dry loan condition: no option or obligation to purchase. He still has a future at Real Madrid and both him &amp; the club agreed that he must get a considerable number of games under his belt.&rdquo;

Dharmesh Sheth (Sky reporter) on Tierney: &ldquo;Celtic are, it&rsquo;s not so much rejecting the amount of the bid, I think &pound;25m Celtic would take, but it&rsquo;s the actual structure of the payments &amp; this is all married alongside Arsenal&rsquo;s limited transfer budget, we&rsquo;ve been told.&rdquo; #afc<br />
<br />
Dharmesh Sheth (Sky reporter): &ldquo;They [Arsenal] want to spend as little as they can upfront whereas Celtic want the majority of that &pound;25m paid upfront so they can then in turn go out &amp; buy some players. Arsenal, it looks they&rsquo;ve got an increased confidence they can get Tierney.&rdquo;
